New scirpt replacing v4l2src with customized compiled GST plugin (norisrc)

  New files

  - scirpts/gst_common.py — shared module with validate_jpeg, make_jpeg_probe, and run_preview (the bus-watch / main-loop / signal-handling runner)
  - scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py — norisrc single-camera launcher

  Modified

  - scirpts/gst_uvc_single_cam.py — now imports from gst_common instead of duplicating JPEG validation and the pipeline runner

  Key design decisions in the norisrc script

  1. No framerate in default caps filter — norisrc's get_caps() truncates float fps → int (line 667 of gstnorisrc.cpp: (gint) vi->f_Fps), so 27.5fps becomes 27/1. Rather than guessing
  the truncated value, the default caps are just image/jpeg,width=5120,height=3840 and GStreamer negotiates the framerate from whatever the SDK reports. The --fps flag lets you pin it
  explicitly if needed.
  2. Device selection via --device-index — the SDK device count is internal to the element (only checked in start()). No way to enumerate from Python without creating a pipeline. The
  element gives a clear error if the index is out of range.
  3. Camera controls as optional CLI flags — --trigger-mode, --sensor-shutter, --sensor-gain are only included in the pipeline string when specified. Properties applied at set_caps
  time via nori_apply_controls().

  Usage examples:
  python3 scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py                              # defaults: index=0, 5120x3840, fps auto
  python3 scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py --device-index 1             # second camera
  python3 scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py --fps 27                     # pin framerate
  python3 scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py --trigger-mode hardware      # HW trigger
  python3 scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py --sink fakesink              # decode benchmark
  python3 scirpts/gst_nori_single_cam.py --width 1920 --height 1080   # override resolution
